Turkish Equity Movers: Bank Asya, Nurol, Park, Tupras, THY Move

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-03-11T16:09:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/turkish-equity-movers-componenta-nurol-park-elektrik-move.html
  Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  rose 612.45, or 1 percent, to 63,781.67 at the 5:30 p.m.
close of trading in Istanbul, bringing the week’s gain to 4.4
percent.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Asya Katilim Bankasim AS (ASYAB TI), an Islamic bank, rose
2.8 percent to 2.96 liras, the highest level in two months. The
lender said in a statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange today
that it hadn’t decided to sell a stake or didn’t hire an
investment bank to find a buyer. Reuters reported on March 9
HSBC Holdings Plc had been hired to find a Turkish partner for a
foreign bank, and the Haberturk newspaper said yesterday Qatar
Islamic Bank wants to buy a 25 percent stake in the Asya.    Nurol Gayrimenkul Yatirim Ortakligi AS (NUGYO)  , a real
estate investment trust, rose 25 kurus, or 6.1 percent, to 4.37
liras after saying in a statement to the exchange that it signed
a 111.8 million-lira ($70.5 million) contract with the Turkish
housing authority.  Park Elektrik Uretim Madencilik Sanayi & Ticaret AS (PRKME
TI), a power producer and miner, climbed 22 kurus, or 6 percent,
to 3.87 liras. The company reported profit for 2010 of 37.2
million liras, up from 19.4 million liras a year ago.  Tupras Turkiye Petrol Rafineleri AS (TUPRS TI), Turkey’s
sole refiner, rose the most since Aug. 21, adding 2.20 liras, or
5.6 percent, to 41.60 liras after saying it will pay a gross
dividend on April 4 of 2.98 liras a share.    Turk Hava Yollari (THYAO)  AS, the national airline,
increased 9 kurus, or 2 percent, to 4.59 liras after Serbian
minister Sulejman Ugljanin said in Istanbul that  Turkish
Airlines  was studying the assets of  Serbia ’s JAT Airlines and
may own a majority stake under any deal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Ankara 
